    "problem_statement": "You run a two-factory manufacturing pipeline. Factory A makes components, then Factory B finishes the same jobs.\nEach factory is its own job shop with one-job-per-machine exclusivity and no preemption.\nEvery job must finish all of its Factory A operations before that same job may start any Factory B operation.\nYour objective is to minimize the coupled makespan: the time when the final Factory B operation finishes.\n\nInstance size: 5 jobs, 6 machines in each factory.\nJobs and ordered operations:\n- Job 1: Factory A MA5 (4) -> MA3 (7) -> MA6 (9) -> MA4 (2) -> MA1 (4) -> MA2 (1); Factory B MB2 (4) -> MB1 (7) -> MB6 (5) -> MB5 (3) -> MB4 (7) -> MB3 (3)\n- Job 2: Factory A MA1 (6) -> MA2 (4) -> MA4 (9) -> MA6 (4) -> MA3 (3) -> MA5 (4); Factory B MB1 (7) -> MB2 (5) -> MB5 (1) -> MB6 (6) -> MB3 (7) -> MB4 (3)\n- Job 3: Factory A MA2 (8) -> MA3 (6) -> MA1 (3) -> MA6 (8) -> MA5 (8) -> MA4 (3); Factory B MB5 (1) -> MB3 (5) -> MB1 (1) -> MB2 (6) -> MB6 (7) -> MB4 (1)\n- Job 4: Factory A MA5 (2) -> MA4 (6) -> MA3 (5) -> MA2 (1) -> MA1 (7) -> MA6 (2); Factory B MB3 (4) -> MB5 (6) -> MB6 (9) -> MB4 (6) -> MB2 (3) -> MB1 (6)\n- Job 5: Factory A MA3 (3) -> MA5 (1) -> MA1 (2) -> MA2 (9) -> MA6 (7) -> MA4 (1); Factory B MB2 (4) -> MB1 (6) -> MB6 (5) -> MB3 (8) -> MB4 (7) -> MB5 (3)\n\nConstraints:\n- A machine handles at most one job at a time.\n- Each job must respect its listed operation order inside each factory.\n- Factory B job Jx cannot start until Factory A job Jx has fully completed.\n- When you emit a schedule, every required operation must appear exactly once.\n\nA deterministic feasible baseline schedule is provided below. If you stop immediately or fail to produce a valid schedule, this baseline is what gets scored.\nBaseline makespan: 164\nBaseline schedule summary:\nFactory A: MA1: J1[22-26],J2[26-32],J3[58-61],J4[92-99],J5[99-101]; MA2: J1[26-27],J2[32-36],J3[36-44],J4[91-92],J5[101-110]; MA3: J1[4-11],J2[49-52],J3[52-58],J4[86-91],J5[91-94]; MA4: J1[20-22],J2[36-45],J3[77-80],J4[80-86],J5[117-118]; MA5: J1[0-4],J2[52-56],J3[69-77],J4[77-79],J5[94-95]; MA6: J1[11-20],J2[45-49],J3[61-69],J4[99-101],J5[110-117]\nFactory B: MB1: J1[31-38],J2[56-63],J3[87-88],J4[129-135],J5[135-141]; MB2: J1[27-31],J2[63-68],J3[88-94],J4[126-129],J5[129-133]; MB3: J1[53-56],J2[75-82],J3[82-87],J4[101-105],J5[146-154]; MB4: J1[46-53],J2[82-85],J3[101-102],J4[120-126],J5[154-161]; MB5: J1[43-46],J2[68-69],J3[80-81],J4[105-111],J5[161-164]; MB6: J1[38-43],J2[69-75],J3[94-101],J4[111-120],J5[141-146]\nMakespan: 164\n",
